      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Adelaide 27 April 1891 ¶ Baron Sir F von Mueller ¶ Government Botanist ¶ Melbourne ¶ Dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.04.27a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Herbert Hughes</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ficus</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">carica</seg> (MEL 274373). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 29/4/91'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Adelaide 27 April 1891</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Sir F von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I received your favour<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to H. Hughes, 19 April 1891 (in this edition as 91-04-19a).</p>
               </note> in due course and feel thankful for your very excellent explanations of the question previously submitted to W Botting Hemsley. I will comply with your request and have your letter printed for distribution.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See B91.05.02.</p>
               </note> — I have I believe found a tree of <name key="Caprifoliacea">Caprifoliacea</name>, and post to you a small paper Box contg.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">containing.</p>
               </note> Three green fruits two leaves attached to stems, also several fallen dry fruits and, I hope, you may find the Gallflowers that are so important — the tree that I refer to is growing in one of the oldest formed gardens near Adelaide: quite overgrown by various trees, and there are many fig trees in this garden, all vary in fruit and leaves, therefore I conclude they have all been raised from seeds of Smyrna figs I will forward dried leaves of Capri figs separate post<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also B92.14.04.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H B Hughes</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Caprifoliacea">Caprifoliacea</name>
            </p>
